Why wouldn't we make it
straight he asks?

15:07.243 --> 15:09.576
Take a closer look.

15:12.392 --> 15:13.550
Uh!

15:13.640 --> 15:15.251
Let me elucidate.

15:15.253 --> 15:18.571
In case you haven't
heard, this undertaking

15:18.636 --> 15:22.050
is being subsidized by the enormous
teat of the federal government.

15:22.052 --> 15:25.058
This never-ending,
money-gushing nipple

15:25.061 --> 15:28.334
pays me
$16,000 per mile,

15:28.391 --> 15:32.514
yet, you build
my road straight!

15:37.834 --> 15:39.956
You're fired.
Get out.

15:41.668 --> 15:45.802
I said, get out.

15:51.469 --> 15:55.283
You look like
a bright young man.

16:27.391 --> 16:29.553
This land...

16:29.631 --> 16:32.830
It's bewitching.

16:32.877 --> 16:37.704
It hasn't changed since Lewis and
Clark first saw it 60 years ago.

16:37.751 --> 16:41.150
Do you ever wonder
if our work here will...

16:41.222 --> 16:43.635
Will be the ruin
of all of this?

16:43.704 --> 16:46.260
Progress comes
with a cost, lily.

16:46.359 --> 16:50.454
I just think it's so much more
beautiful without people.

16:51.209 --> 16:52.715
Don't fool yourself.

16:52.776 --> 16:54.151
There are plenty
of people here.

16:54.225 --> 16:57.342
We're entering
Cheyenne territory.

16:57.344 --> 16:58.712
You do remember
our agreement?

17:00.076 --> 17:01.656
You mean our agreement
to regarding

17:01.741 --> 17:03.953
my not leaving your side
while you were ill?

17:03.955 --> 17:05.192
No.

17:05.259 --> 17:06.618
Ahem.

17:06.671 --> 17:11.714
I mean, our agreement
that you should go back

17:11.770 --> 17:15.589
to Chicago once we entered
hostile Indian territory.

17:16.791 --> 17:19.103
Yes, my dear, but it was
before you took ill.

17:19.180 --> 17:20.718
Yeah.

17:20.868 --> 17:23.348
I believe our second agreement
supersedes our first.

17:23.415 --> 17:26.087
