30:16.627 --> 30:17.949
Send it.

30:29.297 --> 30:30.666
You need some water.

30:30.715 --> 30:35.132
No, it ain't... it ain't
break time yet.

30:35.203 --> 30:39.203
Come on, you need
some water. Come on.

30:43.543 --> 30:45.882
Come on.

30:47.234 --> 30:48.599
Unh.

30:54.409 --> 30:57.490
I thought I told you to dump
that dirt on the other side.

30:57.560 --> 30:59.245
Hey.
Shut your mouth.

30:59.327 --> 31:01.228
I told him to do it.

31:01.279 --> 31:04.196
We going to fill in that
dip over yonder next.

31:04.251 --> 31:07.082
I figured we might just use
some field dirt nearby.

31:10.341 --> 31:14.379
You talk to me before any
decisions are made, all right?

31:14.430 --> 31:16.583
Yes, sir, master.

31:16.625 --> 31:18.511
What did you say?

31:18.580 --> 31:21.548
Bohannon, what the hell
is going on here?

31:21.601 --> 31:23.599
You drink when
I tell you to drink!

31:26.437 --> 31:28.530
Uh!

31:28.594 --> 31:29.892
Get up!

31:29.943 --> 31:33.785
Willy! Willy! Willy!

31:33.859 --> 31:35.430
Willy!

31:37.365 --> 31:42.122
This is what happens
when you break my rules.

32:35.871 --> 32:39.857
Now, what you planning on doing
with that Arkansas toothpick, huh?

32:41.363 --> 32:43.567
Don't do it.

32:46.212 --> 32:52.577
We ain't on no plantation
no more... walking boss.

32:57.219 --> 33:00.697
Ain't nothing good
gonna come from this.

33:09.205 --> 33:10.926
Yeah.

33:11.079 --> 33:13.369
Well, there ain't nothing
good coming from this either.

33:13.413 --> 33:15.845
That dumb n
actually thought

33:15.847 --> 33:18.387
this was gonna
changed a thing.

33:21.262 --> 33:24.206
Look what that got him.

33:27.280 --> 33:30.963
Might just as well
wipe my ass with it.

33:39.912 --> 33:45.132
You kill him...
You will hang.

33:49.250 --> 33:52.500
How they gonna hang me if
there ain't no witnesses?

33:52.502 --> 33:56.049
You come to me
with a knife, son...

33:56.157 --> 33:58.274
You better be ready to use it.

34:12.761 --> 34:14.636
Yeah.

34:16.420 --> 34:19.947
You got to let
go of the past.

34:21.762 --> 34:24.007
Have you let it go?

35:04.349 --> 35:06.497
You doing quite a trade here.

35:06.499 --> 35:08.927
Not bad for a couple
of Irish bumpkins.

35:09.009 --> 35:10.594
Where's Mickey?

35:10.647 --> 35:15.248
He's preparing
for the grand finale.

35:29.348 --> 35:33.720
** When you're far away

35:33.774 --> 35:39.828
** far from the land
you'll be **

35:39.885 --> 35:47.306
do you not pine for your own
homeland, Mr. Bohannon?

35:49.470 --> 35:50.961
No.

35:52.809 --> 35:55.319
And why is that?

35:57.981 --> 35:59.575
It's gone.

35:59.577 --> 36:01.160
** Bright and fair

36:01.312 --> 36:04.997
** and rich in its treasures

36:05.081 --> 36:07.390
** Muldoon

36:16.711 --> 36:22.931
** Won't you come back soon

36:22.998 --> 36:28.974
** love you

36:32.007 --> 36:35.508
So, tell me, Bohannon...

36:35.720 --> 36:38.966
Did you see the elephant
during the war?

36:38.968 --> 36:41.624
Yes, I saw my share
of action, yeah.

36:41.626 --> 36:43.848
Where?

36:44.981 --> 36:47.851
Yeah. I don't like
to talk about it.

36:51.559 --> 36:53.851
I loved the war.

36:55.034 --> 36:57.490
I loved the war!

37:01.454 --> 37:05.035
The best thing that
ever happened to me.

37:06.264 --> 37:08.369
I thought you said
you were against it?

37:08.432 --> 37:10.333
Oh, yeah, I was.

37:10.400 --> 37:13.744
But... that
doesn't mean...

37:13.873 --> 37:18.350
That I didn't enjoy myself
once pressed into service.

37:18.417 --> 37:20.517
Hey!

37:20.519 --> 37:22.841
Oh, hey,
I'm... I'm skimped.

37:23.047 --> 37:26.427
No, no. This one's on me.

37:26.500 --> 37:30.879
Well... well, thank you.

37:37.286 --> 37:39.833
Most men shrink...

37:39.894 --> 37:42.659
When they see
the elephant up close.

37:42.810 --> 37:44.049
Oh, yeah?

37:44.196 --> 37:47.900
But I... I blossomed.

38:00.921 --> 38:02.910
Thank you.

38:04.059 --> 38:07.060
Though I...

38:07.118 --> 38:10.265
I must admit that
there were, um...

38:11.538 --> 38:13.965
Certain lines
that I crossed.

38:14.025 --> 38:18.919
Lines of morality that I didn't
think myself capable of crossing.

38:29.241 --> 38:33.439
But that's
what men do... in war.

38:33.494 --> 38:35.357
Hmm.

38:37.493 --> 38:39.949
Moral men don't.

38:43.549 --> 38:47.318
So, you did nothing that
you were ashamed of?

38:50.578 --> 38:54.141
I did plenty I was ashamed of.

39:03.179 --> 39:06.705
You ever been to Meridian,
Mississippi, Mr. Johnson?

39:12.790 --> 39:16.348
That is my remington
pointed at your gut.

39:16.413 --> 39:20.837
So... let's take
a walk out back.

39:28.009 --> 39:33.775
I know about the 2 men
you killed in Maryland.

39:33.842 --> 39:35.698
I read in the paper
about Prescott

39:35.778 --> 39:39.943
getting killed in that
church by a griswold.

39:41.282 --> 39:43.361
But I'll be damned
if you didn't show up

39:43.397 --> 39:45.990
a few days later with a griswold
strapped to your hip as plain as day.

39:46.026 --> 39:50.898
And then you ask me about
Meridian? That's sensitive.

39:52.017 --> 39:54.961
Mmm! I am not proud

39:55.021 --> 39:58.093
of what happened
to your wife, Bohannon.

39:58.153 --> 40:00.639
It didn't happen to her.

40:00.718 --> 40:03.030
You did it to her.

40:04.468 --> 40:07.885
Yes. Yes,
we did it to her.

40:07.975 --> 40:10.546
I did it to her.

40:11.981 --> 40:16.212
Your wife was in the wrong
place at the wrong time.

40:19.591 --> 40:22.437
I want you to know...

40:22.578 --> 40:26.404
It wasn't my idea
to kill her.

40:26.449 --> 40:29.403
She hung herself?

40:30.573 --> 40:32.529
No, she didn't.

40:32.592 --> 40:36.100
The sergeant strangled
her and strung her up.

40:36.104 --> 40:38.007
Sergeant?

40:38.087 --> 40:40.407
What sergeant?

40:42.218 --> 40:43.705
Well,
he's out here, too.

40:43.760 --> 40:46.589
I figured you were
saving him for last.

40:49.932 --> 40:53.361
Oh, you didn't
know about it?

40:53.433 --> 40:55.418
You tell me who he is.

40:55.491 --> 40:57.436
Well, it hardly
matters now.

40:57.638 --> 40:59.089
No!

41:07.974 --> 41:09.400
Tell me his name.

41:12.605 --> 41:14.281
Tell me his name.

41:25.151 --> 41:26.824
Is it a villain you want?

41:26.911 --> 41:28.952
I'll play the part.

41:33.276 --> 41:36.059
After all, what is a
drama without a villain?

41:36.298 --> 41:42.474
What is the building of this
grand road if not a drama?

41:44.327 --> 41:48.315
This business is not
for the weak of heart.

41:49.347 --> 41:52.295
It's a thorny,
brutal affair

41:52.346 --> 41:57.469
that rewards the lion
for his ferocity.

41:58.468 --> 42:00.317
What of the zebra?

42:00.450 --> 42:02.739
What of the poor zebra?

42:02.801 --> 42:06.975
Well, the zebra's eaten
as the zebra should be.

42:08.360 --> 42:11.409
Make no mistake.
Blood will be spilled.

42:11.484 --> 42:13.497
Lives will be lost.

42:13.583 --> 42:15.250
Fortunes will be made.

42:15.319 --> 42:17.249
Men will be ruined.

42:17.319 --> 42:21.840
There will be
betrayal and scandal.

42:21.893 --> 42:24.422
A perfidy
of epic proportions.

42:24.424 --> 42:31.678
But... the lion
shall prevail.

42:33.103 --> 42:38.137
You see, the secret
I know is this...

42:38.191 --> 42:44.018
All of history
is driven by the lion.

42:44.067 --> 42:49.535
We drag the poor zebra
kicking and braying.

42:51.236 --> 42:57.054
Stain the earth
with his cheap blood.

42:57.127 --> 43:02.300
History doesn't
remember us fondly,

43:02.362 --> 43:06.542
but then history is written
by the zebra for the zebra.

43:09.370 --> 43:12.875
100 years hence...

43:12.923 --> 43:17.211
When this railroad
spans the continent

43:17.270 --> 43:22.692
and America rises to be the greatest
power the world has seen...

43:22.738 --> 43:31.899
I will be remembered
as a caitiff...

43:31.946 --> 43:34.499
Malefactor...

43:34.559 --> 43:39.835
Who only operated out of
greed for personal gain.

43:39.906 --> 43:43.925
All true. All true.

43:49.656 --> 43:51.627
But remember this...

43:53.774 --> 43:59.425
Without me...
And men like me,

43:59.468 --> 44:02.756
your glorious railroad
would never have been built.

